From sfalcon at fhcrc.org  Thu Sep  6 19:27:28 2007
From: sfalcon at fhcrc.org (Seth Falcon)
Date: Thu, 06 Sep 2007 10:27:28 -0700
Subject: [Bioc-devel] Version numbers for your packages
Message-ID: <m2vean7lhb.fsf@fhcrc.org>

Hello BioC package maintainers,

I want to remind you all of the version number policy:

   http://wiki.fhcrc.org/bioc/Version_Numbering_Standards

Packages that are in the BioC 2.0 release need not take any action; we
will do the version number bumping as part of the release process.

Newly contributed packages must have either:

  1) a version number >= 1.1.0

OR

  2) a version number >= 0.99.0

Option #2 is preferred for new packages because we will bump to 1.0.0
for the release.  Option #1 is fine, but such packages will go to
1.2.0 for release and 1.3.0 for the subsequent devel cycle.

Please post to bioc-devel with questions if you are at all unsure.

Thanks,

+ seth


-- 
